	   <a name=105486304622519></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105486304622519><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=105486304622519>Armor and Lvl</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=105486304622519#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Sage>Yosa</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>147 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 5th 10:11 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.83]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are really only two ways to upgrade your equipment.&nbsp;&nbsp;One is to buy stuff that other have looted the other is to get a group together and go kill the mobs yourself.  Futhermore, most of the time  people have far better equipment than is needed for most pick up groups.  For example in the early days people wore patchwork until the mid teens.  <br>Then upgraded to Rignmail (drops in high hold pass) and Bronze, or Banded.  In group setting this armor can be used until the late 20 or early 30.  <br><br>At which point you should be able to start you Crafted quests.   You should be able to camp the Netherbian Chitin about lvl 20.  By the late 30's to early 40's you should be able to camp the Ry'Gorr which drop armor some consider as good as crafted.  By the Mid 40's you can camp Skyshrine for Sentry and Guarding, which some cnsider an upgrad to crafted.  All of this armor us usable to lvl 50 or higher.  <br><br>At lvl 50 if you can talk a group into it you can get some of the Royal Velium Frosted Armor.  Start hunting Kael for the Quest armor drops.  By the Mid 50's you should be able to Hunt UP for Moktor Armor, and the new LoY zones for Steel Wrapped Armor.  <br>The key thing to remember is a lot of the above armor is no drop and you will almost always need to take your owne group to these zones.  <br><br>Really the funest way to upgrade your eqipment is to hunt with a normal group in the zone that drop the items you want.  Sure you will still need/want to buy some items, but you will have far more money to spend, since you looted most of equipment.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
