	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105481338418282><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=105481338418282>RE: Awful twink</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=105481338418282#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=103498><span id=Sage>kdsktan</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>120 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 5th 8:23 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Theres not really much you can do if you have started out just recently, as you probably have. I know you probably see a lot of warriors running around with very good gear but these are most likely the alternate characters of high level players who have money to burn.<br><br>What I will say is this. Dont worry. You can get by fine with the equipment that you have at the moment, especially if its 5-6kpp worth. With the bazaar these days that can get you a decent set of gear which should see you through to the 50s.<br><br>Once you get to the 50s /60s, thats when you really do have the opportunity to start making more money - either by exp grouping in places with nice cash drops, or farming lower end areas.<br><br>Anyway, i do definitely think you can make more than 50pp per hour for sure. Heres a few pointers for easy money - you want to get stuff that tradeskillers need and are willing to pay for. This is stuff that will always sell the easiest rather than trying for items which no one wants to buy these days and which will stay stuck on your trader.<br><br>So, go to places like crystal caverns and farm acrylia bricks and silks. I know bricks of acrylia sell for 50pp to 100 pp each on my server and you can get a few of these easy per hour. Alternatively hunt in places like Great divide killing giants - they drop weapons and plat, or rathe mountains with the hill giants. <br><br>The thing to remember is this - the place with the best experience is not necessarily where you make themost money. eg. now the best exp is PoP, but its not very good for money. The bestmoney i ever used to make was in old sebilis where i could clear 1-2k pp anight from gems and item drops in a regular group.<br><br>So, go and spend a couple of hours in the bazaar and see what tradeskill components are selling for. Youd be surprised how much an item which you may have thought was junk and destroyed goes for, because simply, a level 65 tradeskiller would rather pay 50pp for it than go farm a green zone.<br><br>Gulug<br>64 Warlord<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
