	   <tr><td colspan=2>At first glance you look good, but your HP’s are a bit low.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also appears that you’re concentrating on getting your STR up as high as possible, which is ok, as long as you’re not overlooking options that might get you a better AC or more HP’s. If you’re tanking AC and HP’s are key.<br><br>I'm not sure if it's considered a step up or not, but I happen to prefer the Crusty armor (Crustacean) over the Validus. The AC is really close, but the stat modifiers are much, much better. You get a lot of HP's from all that STA which is a big deal when tanking. The 8 crusy pieces give you 87 STA which is a few hundred HP's.  You also lose a lot of AGI with the Validus, which means you'll be hit a bit more often.  Granted, crusty makes you ugly CHA wise, but you're a warrior and we're supposed to be ugly. Plus, you can take the gear off when buying stuff from merchants.<br><br>As for other stuff - There are some rings out there that give you some pretty nice HP's.<br>Type “wedding ring” into the item search engine on this site and you’ll get a number of options at various price points.  <br><br>Maybe Bikamar and Kdsktan can add their $.02. They always seem to give good advice.<br><br>Good luck,<br><br>Roos<br>Barb Warr 43<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=624944" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=624944</a><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
