	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I just went on my first raid last night and loved it.&nbsp;&nbsp;A pick-up raid on the dragon Vox.  Yes, I died, but we killed her &amp; I was one of the very last ones to die (20 of 36 died) I died only because I accidentally hit my taunt hotkey.  Oops!!!   Once was all it took. Pulled agro, chomp, chomp, chomp, one dead me.  As a lower level tank it was a fatal mistake.<br><br>Chalk it up to experience. Anyway, I now realize that if I want to do more raids on any sort of regular basis I'm going to have to join a guild. But the question is which one to join? I have a number of friends in guilds, but they are all small/mid-size guilds that almost never raid – more like social clubs or cooperatives.  <br><br>So I have to look for information on guilds elsewhere.   I'm having a hard time finding any good reference information on guilds and the various options, how big they are, how often they raid, level qualifications for joining, etc.<br><br>I don't want everyone to respond by saying &quot;Woot, my guild is best....&quot;  Cause I'm sure they are all good in their own way.  I’m just looking for a method to evaluate my options.<br><br>Here's what I'm looking for - good sized guild where they raid a few times a week but have enough members that they won't get bent if I can't attend more than 2-4 raids a month. I don't want a guild too into the role-playing thing (not my style) or too into that whole EQ marriage thing (one more aspect of the game I don't get - I have a RL wife, sure don't need another one in EQ!!)  Just looking for a large bunch of good, fun players/smart people who like to kill stuff and help each other out on occasion.<br><br>I don’t want to be one of those people who hop around between guilds, so I want to make a smart choice up front.  On to my question:  Have any of you been in this situation and how did you end up selecting a guild? What are the best resources to research the guild options on Saryrn? Are there web sites where most of the guilds post information? Does Verant publish guild lists with sizes?  And lastly since many of you are in guilds and I’m not, what are important qualities that you think I should look for in a guild<br><br>Any insights would be appreciated.<br>Thanks,<br><br>Roos<br>Barb Warr 43<br>Saryrn<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
