	   <tr><td colspan=2>Theres another reason to think about 2hb. The current flavour of the month as far as warrior 2handers are concerned is the greatstaff of thunder. it procs stun and gets a lot of aggro and for 40k or so, its really worth the money. you will find at the higher end game that its all about aggro and theres not a lot of weapons that you can buy for that kind of money to get similar aggro.<br><br>So if possible, get a selection of all weps and train them up. You dont necessarily have to max em at all times, just keep them ticking over. Then, if you do find a nice weapon you are happy to stick with, it wont take much to max it out. Just dont find yourself in my situation now, when im looking to maybe get myself a GSOT at lvl 63 and my 2hb is at 60 or thereabouts.<br><br>Gulug<br>63 Warlord<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
