	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another thing you need to learn is the pathing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some camps are set up so mobs run out of them along a certain path.  When you shoot the mob does it run past and trigger other mobs, or does it come strate out towards you.  some rooms/camps can be pulled clockwise other need to be pulled counter clock wise.  Others you just need to make sure you are targeting the mob nearest to you. <br>Also some mobs such as door gaurds etc, can be very hard to solo pull.  This is when you need to have someone root one and you pull the other far enough away that when the root drops the mob don't come after the rooter.  Also having someone lull or harmanize is a key to solo pulling mobs.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
