	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off i hope your using a bow to pull. It helps get some damage in and gives you a bit of running space.<br><br>Theres no real &quot;art&quot; to pulling. It just comes with practice. Just get a feel for the zone and the aggro range of the mobs. When your sure that the mob is outside the aggro/assist range of others, then tag it. <br><br>That isnt the end of the story though. When heading back to camp, always check theres no mobs in your path on the way back. If there are, then youll have to detour and bring your mob with you. <br><br>Its really all a question for just being aware of whats around. However, even with the best will in the world you will always get an add or two, but thats what casters/enchanters are for.<br><br><br>Gulug<br>63 Warlord<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
