	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 25th 10:05 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, if you want to solo, pick a class that is good at it. Druids, Necromancers, shamans, mages, etc. are better suited to solo than warriors, paladins, wizards, etc. Im not saying that any class isn't able to solo, just that some are easier than others. So rather than whine about it, use your brain. You are allowed 8 characters per server. Make at least two characters of different classes, one that can solo easily and another that is better in a group. If you feel like grouping, play the second one. If you want to play alone, or can't find a group at that precise moment, play the first one. Why is this so hard?<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun May 25 21:24:22 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
