<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=105361449428291></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105361449428291><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=105361449428291>Observation -  and a minor vent.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=105361449428291#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=210062><span id=Scholar>Stabo</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>46 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 22nd 11:23 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I've got my first character - a warrior - up to level 42 and I've made the following observation.&nbsp;&nbsp;( I expect to get flamed a bit for making it.)<br><br>I think warriors are probably the most disadvantaged class in this game.  Don't get me wrong, I love playing my warrior, it's just that it feels as though - balance wise - the game favors those who can cast or at least have some casting ability.<br><br>Now if you look at the role a warrior plays in a well-balanced group, at the higher levels we play a critical part - punching bag - that few others can assume.  But how much of the game is actually played in these situations?  <br><br>The flexibility that I see other classes have with regard to playing style I somewhat envy. Assuming you have a job, or school and a life outside of the game, and don’t want to jump in and out of groups as your schedule permits, soloing with a warrior is a pain, plain and simple. Recovering from tough battles can take forever.<br><br>I think when the game was created, it was assumed that people would be grouping most of the time - it being incented with group exp bonus's etc.  But the playing style of the various classes has evolved over the years as individual have discovered the best ways to play their class.  Kiting, DoTing, whatever the strategies, the advantages of the classes have been discovered. But inherently in the warrior class there isn't that much &quot;new strategy&quot; that we can employ. As a result, I think that to some extent as the other classes have developed creative soloing methods, we have fallen behind the others somewhat from a balance standpoint.  Maybe the difference is that warriors are more one dimensional – tanks – while other classes are more multi-dimensional and can play a variety of different roles, depending on whether they are in a group or not.<br><br>Here I am trying to get my HP's as high as I can so that I'll be a better tank, but the higher my HP's get the longer it takes to heal up when I'm down to 10%. (granted it takes me longer to get down to 10% but that's besides the point.)  Most other classes are running circles around me soloing on the battlefield.  (Ok, this is turning into a longer vent than I had intended, but I might as well finish.)<br><br>So here's my solution:<br>I seriously think that the recovery rate for warriors should go up as their levels go up. Look at it this way, if you took me and some decorated Green Beret and beat us both down hard - to almost dead - I sure and hell don't believe I'd be back at 100% strength faster than he would - that's BS.  His recovery rate from training and fitness should be many times faster than mine. (And I'm in good shape!!)<br><br>Translated into the game, it should not take a lvl 50 warrior 2, 3, or 4 times longer to recover from a near death experience than it does a lvl 5 warrior.<br><br>This improvement in recovery rate would go a long way toward balancing out the warrior class with the others, by significantly reducing our down time.  I'm not suggesting a huge number, but even a 5-10 hp's per tick at the highest levels would make a dramatic improvement. We would still need healers when tanking in groups because the improved recovery rate would not come close to the damage a big mob or multiple mobs can deal.<br><br>One last thing, I know that the casters need to recharge their mana, which can take some time, but since everyone has KEI these days, it sure doesn't compare to the waiting that we warriors have to endure.<br><br>And once again, don’t get me wrong, I love being a warrior – I love the pulling, the tanking – it’s all a blast. I just wish we could hold our own a little better.<br><br>Roos<br>Barb Warr 42<br>Saryrn<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
