	   <tr><td colspan=2>Also, lets not forget there are other classes who are trying to take our jobs as tanks. Specially when you reach high levels, you'll see other classes taking your aggro and saying, &quot;Woot I'm a tank!&quot; This may be all in good fun but after awhile it can get frustrating. I'm sure it has happend to all of us. Also, everyone seems to be leading towards hps. Hps are good but don't forget about your ac. Don't get me wrong, I can hold aggro pretty well in exp groups and in raids. There will always be that one group member who will be able to take aggro from you. Weather its a heal from a cleric, or a shammys/enchies slow, or that rogue/ranger/monk with epic haste. <br><br>I love being a warrior though, our job is to take damage, not dish it out. People seem to forget that. We don't have any casting abilities but we have a wide viarity of weapons at our disposale. We have some pretty mean disciplens and helpfull AA abilities. You won't see a paladin or shadowknight tanking those big mean gods. There was a time when we warriors were the most sought after of for exp groups. Now its Palys and Sks. Things have changed for better or for worse. We warriors will have to accept the changes and find a way to become the best part in exp groups. Allthough I think we still rock in exp groups, there are others who think otherwise. Anyways, I still think we're a great class, but with the recent improvments to the other &quot;tank&quot; classes, SoE needs to do something for us quick, perhapes give us innate haste as a AA ability or triple attack. Or even more base hps. <br><br>Takata K'Trazz<br>LVL 61 Darkelf Warlord<br>Emarr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251453" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251453</a><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri May 23 12:35:39 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
