	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just ran into exactly the same problem in DSP.&nbsp;&nbsp;I went from 32-42 primarily in that zone and loved it.  Though I have to say I grouped (ME &amp; GE camps) most of the time.  At 42 the tribals are now light blue to me, so I'm not hunting them anymore.  <br><br>I did get a very good suggestion from another warrior in the zone who seemed to be leveling a lot quicker than I was.  He was pairing with a healer - druid, cleric, or shammy - and hunting large Zelniks.  He was pulling two at a time and fighting non-stop. They go down easy and provide good exp.  In 4 hours doing this I managed a whole level from 41-42.  He said it was good up to 45, when they con'd light blue.<br><br>As for other areas to hunt, my friends and I have just started hunting the Dreadlands and like it quite a bit. Good visibility, tons of mobs, easy to get in trouble if you're not careful - plenty of risk - and camps usually looking for additional members.  The exp has been good, but we've only worked the area a couple days now and I haven't sold what I've looted, so I'm not sure if the loot is valuable or not.<br><br>If you're looking for loot, not many places beat the Rathe Mountain hill giants - 20-50 pp/kill - though you have to deal with all the others trying to pull them also.<br><br>Good luck,<br><br>Roos<br>Barb Warr 42<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
